article.description: Micah Seaborn scored 20 points and Monmouth topped Quinnipiac 88-74 on Saturday.
article.headline: Monmouth tops Quinnipiac 88-74
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. -- Micah Seaborn scored 20 points and Monmouth topped Quinnipiac 88-74 on Saturday. Seaborn was just 4 of 12 from the floor, but went 10 of 12 at the line for the Hawks (11-4, 3-1 Metro Atlantic). Chris Brady had 16 points and 13 rebounds, Justin Robinson scored 15 and Deon Jones added 11. Quinnipiac (5-9, 2/3 Metro Atlantic) was paced by Daniel Harris with 19 points. Giovanni McLean scored 15 points while Abdulai Bundu added 12 points and 12 rebounds. Seaborn's late first-half 3-pointer helped Monmouth lead 37-35 at intermission. A seven-point run midway through the second put Monmouth up by double-digits. Monmouth's last 18 points all came at the free throw line in the last three minutes of the game. Quinnipiac committed 33 fouls and Monmouth was 38 of 50 from the line.
